      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 836: setPublishedAddressSettings always writes both publishedAddress and publishedPort, even when only one field changed or neither changed. This can cause unnecessary daemon reconfiguration and may overwrite concurrent/local detail changes with stale UI state. Mirror setStunSettings/setTurnSettings behavior by only including changed keys before calling setAccountDetails.\n```suggestion\n        var detailsToUpdate \u003d [String: String]()\n        for (key, value) in settings {\n            let property \u003d ConfigKeyModel(withKey: key)\n            guard details.get(withConfigKeyModel: property) !\u003d value else { continue }\n            details.set(withConfigKeyModel: property, withValue: value)\n            detailsToUpdate[key.rawValue] \u003d value\n        }\n\n        guard !detailsToUpdate.isEmpty else { return }\n        let changed \u003d AccountConfigModel(withDetails: detailsToUpdate)\n        self.setAccountDetails(forAccountId: accountId, withDetails: changed)\n```",
